-23|language=en-GB|archive-date=2022-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121230322/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-54969682|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=A Chinese citizen journalist who was detained after reporting on the government's coronavirus response could spend five years in prison for it|url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/zhang-zhan-arrested-covid-19-wuhan-risk-5-years-prison-2020-12|accessdate=2020-12-23|date=2020-12-06|last=Baker|first=Sinéad|work=Business Insider Australia|language=en|archive-date=2021-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211104191406/https://www.businessinsider.com.au/zhang-zhan-arrested-covid-19-wuhan-risk-5-years-prison-2020-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Citizen journalist could be jailed for reporting on COVID-19 outbreak in Wuhan|url=https://thehill.com/changing-america/respect/526125-citizen-journalist-could-be-jailed-for-reporting-on-covid-19|accessdate=2020-12-23|date=2020-11-16|last=Guzman|first=Joseph|work=TheHill|language=en|archive-date=2021-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210510024518/https://thehill.com/changing-america/respect/526125-citizen-journalist-could-be-jailed-for-reporting-on-covid-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>

